The Western Cape Health Department has been on a two-day tour showcasing the state of readiness of its hotspot areas. The national health delegation got a chance to see various facilities that will serve as field hospitals in the province. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The total number of confirmed positive COVID-19 cases in South Africa stands at 35,812 with 755 deaths. The health department announced that a total of 761,534 tests have been conducted to date. Level 3 lockdown: Cameras help curb COVID-19 spread Recoveries stand at 18,313. The Western Cape still has the highest number of positive cases with 23,583 cases followed by the Eastern Cape with 4,324 cases and Gauteng with 4,276 cases. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.